1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Science has a clearer story about encoding specificity than social media does.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:11,200
Encoding specificity explains why we remember things better in the same context where we learned them.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,600
Imagine studying in a coffee shop.

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:18,400
You might ace the test there, but struggle in a quiet classroom.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,400
Research shows that matching the environment during recall enhances memory.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,400
It’s not just a coincidence!

7
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:28,400
So, next time you study, think about where you are.

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,800
Your memory might thank you later.

